    id: 'lost-city-meridian',
    title: 'The Lost City of Meridian',
    genre: 'Adventure / Fantasy',
    kidSafeText: `Three years ago, Elena found a special map in her grandmother's attic. The map showed a hidden city called Meridian, deep in the jungle. Most people said it was just a story, but Elena believed it was real.

Elena gathered a team of five friends to help her find the city. They packed their bags and headed into the jungle. The journey was hard—there were thick vines, big bugs, and lots of rain. But Elena's team kept going, following the map's clues.

After two weeks, they found special markers along the way. Each marker looked like an animal carved in stone. Marco, their guide, said his grandmother's grandmother had told stories about this place. "The people who built this city loved the jungle," he said.

On the sixteenth day, something amazing happened. The jungle opened up, and there it was—Meridian! The city had beautiful white buildings that seemed to glow. Gardens with colorful flowers grew everywhere. It looked like the city and the jungle were friends, growing together.

Elena and her team explored the city. They found libraries with books that hadn't turned to dust, even after hundreds of years. In the main plaza, they found a message carved in stone. When they figured out what it said, it read: "We built this city to teach. Remember: we are part of the jungle, and the jungle is part of us."

Elena realized something wonderful. The people of Meridian hadn't disappeared because something bad happened. They had chosen to return to the jungle, leaving their city as a gift—a reminder that people and nature can live together in harmony.

Elena and her team carefully documented everything they found. They knew this discovery would help people understand that we can build amazing things while still taking care of the world around us. The Lost City of Meridian wasn't just a place—it was a lesson about living wisely.`,
